  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Beisboleritos (little baseballers) began in Medellin in 2009 as an initiative to counter the presence of illegal groups affecting children and adolescents in Colombia. These children become a target for illegal armed groups (guerrilla) through armed recruitment, making them child soldiers. Beisboleritos works in highly vulnerable communities to help children and adolescents develop and strengthen skills to resist and assertively respond to these threats. Info: info@gipcolombia.org</narrative>
  </description>
